column5: Hey all, Was thinking about crossing into Fort Frances late on Saturday afternoon what would it be like then ? Usually we cross over on Fridays early no problem, but because of schedule conflict will not be getting into camp until Sunday. BOB
You will be fine, I cross last saturday in the late afternoon and there was only 1 vehicle in front of me.
I've crossed on Saturday afternoon the last two years and the crossing went fast.
Anytime after 3PM there isn't much of a wait
I came through from Canada last night (Sunday) at about 4:30 and the wait was about 10 minutes. Looked like the wiat going into Canda was about the same.
I think the "busiest" time is typically late morning/early afternoon. (We have had to wait up to 3 hours some years).
